title: shouldi: Unable to export the dataflow of shouldi
body:
## Steps To Reproduce

What were you doing when the bug happened.

I was trying [this](https://intel.github.io/dffml/master/tutorials/operations.html?highlight=new%20operations%20tutorial#visualizing-the-dataflow) in a fresh branch and it throws this error

```console
gitpod /workspace/dffml/examples/shouldi $ dffml service dev export -configloader json shouldi.cli:DATAFLOW   > shouldi/deploy/df/shouldi.json
Traceback (most recent call last):
  File "/home/gitpod/.pyenv/versions/3.8.2/bin/dffml", line 11, in <module>
    load_entry_point('dffml', 'console_scripts', 'dffml')()
  File "/workspace/dffml/dffml/util/cli/cmd.py", line 273, in main
    result = loop.run_until_complete(cls._main(*argv[1:]))
  File "/home/gitpod/.pyenv/versions/3.8.2/lib/python3.8/asyncio/base_events.py", line 616, in run_until_complete
    return future.result()
  File "/workspace/dffml/dffml/util/cli/cmd.py", line 234, in _main
    result = await cls.cli(*args)
  File "/workspace/dffml/dffml/util/cli/cmd.py", line 220, in cli
    return await cmd.do_run()
  File "/workspace/dffml/dffml/util/cli/cmd.py", line 202, in do_run
    return await self.run()
  File "/workspace/dffml/dffml/service/dev.py", line 277, in run
    for obj in load(self.export, relative=os.getcwd()):
  File "/workspace/dffml/dffml/util/entrypoint.py", line 43, in load
    obj = getattr(obj, attr)
AttributeError: module 'json' has no attribute ''
```

## Expected behavior
get a json file of shouldi dataflow
